Name: Trainee
Description: Someone who is studying or finishing their studies and does not have professional experience. This level requires supervision and is usually accompanied by training and monitoring of other members of the organization.

Name: Junior
Description: One who is starting his professional career and usually has less than two years of experience in the field. He usually needs help to carry out some tasks and has a great capacity for learning.

Name: Mid-Senior
Description: That person who has between 2 to 6 years practicing his profession without interruption. She is self-sufficient and has a good command of her tools and working skills.

Name: Senior
Description: He is a person who has more than 6 years of experience in the field, makes decisions without the need for supervision and can even train other people.
